The paper proposes a novel if-conversion scheme that uses machine learning techniques to optimize program acceleration. This involves customizing if-conversion overall branches within a program, which suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of machine learning techniques also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves experimentation and optimization, which could fall under computer architecture (cs.AR).
